I think I could just have a method to return an int here, but in all non-test cases we'll want to do something like:
LongKeyedBucketOrds impl(Cardinality cardinality) {
  return cardinality.map(estimate -> {
    if (estimate < 2) return new FromSingle();
    if (estimate < Integer.MAX_VALUE) return new FromInts();
    return new FromMany();
  });
}

So map feels fairly natural. Also, it will stop compiling if we ever decide that we need to encode more stuff in the estimate.

